# Issue Conventions

## Title format

```
[TYPE] Short description in English
```

### Allowed types

| Type         | When to use                              |
|--------------|------------------------------------------|
| `[FEAT]`     | New feature or capability                |
| `[BUG]`      | Something is broken                      |
| `[DOCS]`     | Documentation changes                    |
| `[REFACTOR]` | Code restructuring with no new behavior  |
| `[TEST]`     | Adding or improving tests                |
| `[CHORE]`    | Tooling, CI, dependencies, config        |

### Title examples

```
[FEAT] Add JWT authentication
[BUG] Login crashes on empty email input
[DOCS] Add API endpoint reference
[REFACTOR] Extract validation logic into shared module
[CHORE] Upgrade Node.js to v20
```

## Body template (mandatory sections)

Every issue MUST include these sections. Use this exact template:

```
gh issue create --title "[TYPE] Title" --body "$(cat <<'EOF'
## Context
Why this issue exists. What problem does it solve or what need does it address.

## Expected behavior
What should happen once this issue is resolved.

## Acceptance criteria
- [ ] Criterion 1
- [ ] Criterion 2
- [ ] Criterion 3

## Notes
Any technical details, constraints, links, or references.
EOF
)"
```

### Section rules

- **Context**: Required. Explain the motivation, not the implementation.
- **Expected behavior**: Required. Describe the end result from a user or system perspective.
- **Acceptance criteria**: Required. At least one checkbox item. These are used to verify the issue is done.
- **Notes**: Optional but encouraged. Add links, screenshots, technical constraints.

## Labels

Apply at least one label matching the type:

| Type         | Label          |
|--------------|----------------|
| `[FEAT]`     | `enhancement`  |
| `[BUG]`      | `bug`          |
| `[DOCS]`     | `documentation`|
| `[REFACTOR]` | `refactor`     |
| `[TEST]`     | `test`         |
| `[CHORE]`    | `chore`        |

Add the label when creating: `gh issue create --label "enhancement" ...`
